      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KIKI MEISTER (11) finished sixth at Listed level in a race won by Showmethetanlines over 1609m at Menangle when last seen in November. Kicked off that campaign with a Brisbane win so can go well fresh. Tricky draw but goes very well at this distance with three wins and two placings from five attempts. EYE CAN EAR AMOUR (6) turned in a much better run when second up last time out, finishing second over 1609m at Menangle. Meets a comparable field so he can add to the sound recent effort. STEEL STRIDE (10) placed in the city fresh before a last-start win by 8 metres at Canberra. Has upside and could go through the grades. LOOKMEOVER NZ (5) draws lower than last start and should find this easier than recent attempts.",
